info:
You can use the color CSS attribute to specify color of text. <CODE><style>
#MyHeader{
color:red;
}
</style></CODE> Notice the : to split the attribute and the value. Also notice the ; to signify the end of the line. CSS comes with many built in colors, like red, that can be used to style your elements.

You can also use the background-color CSS attribute to specify a background color for your element. <CODE><style>
#MyHeader{
background-color:red;
}
</style></CODE> Again, notice the use of the : and the ;.

